<TITLE> Shab-e-Barat on Aug 6 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 23 (bdnews24.com)--Lailatul Barat, popularly known as Shab-e-Barat, will be observed on the night of August 6. The decision came from a meeting organised by National Moon-Sighting Committee at the conference room of the Islamic Foundation. Islamic Foundation PRO Mohammad Touhidul Anwar told bdnews24.com that the moon was sighted on Thursday in the sky in Sha'ban, 1430. Acting religious ministry secretary and vice president of the committee Mamunur Rashid chaired the meeting. bd
